# Rewrite Porting Order

Mandatory sequence for kernel and subgraph ports. Complements `rewrite-buffer-contract.mdc` for wiring and `rewrite-testing.mdc` for verification.

## Phase 0 - Infrastructure

Current completed substrate:

- Catch2 harness and `nlrc_vksplat_gpu`.
- Headless Vulkan device/queue wrapper: `HeadlessContext`.
- Typed GPU wrappers: `StorageBuffer`, `ComputePipeline`, `StorageBindingList`, `DispatchShape`, `PushConstantsView`.
- Shader embed CMake path.
- Config header plus shader config generator.
- Fixture manifest/load helpers with `BufferSpec`, `BufferDtype`, and typed `load_fixture_buffer<T>()`.

Deferred infrastructure:

- Higher-level full pipeline wrapper that mirrors ref scheduling only after isolated dispatch tests are reliable.

## Phase 1 - Subgraph D

| Order | Kernel | Why |
|-------|--------|-----|
| 1 | `cumsum_*` | Tile indexing, `where`, E/F prune |
| 2 | `sum` | Densification sizing |
| 3 | `where` | Compaction |

## Phase 2 - Radix Sort

Port `radix_sort/*.comp` as one unit: `upsweep -> spine -> downsweep`.

Port before Subgraph A integration. Re-run on `ohos-debug` when available.

## Phase 3 - Subgraph A

| Order | Kernel |
|-------|--------|
| 1 | `projection_forward` |
| 2 | `generate_keys` |
| 3 | `compute_tile_ranges` |
| 4 | `rasterize_forward` |

Gate: wire `forward()` only after all four pass isolated tests. Do not start Subgraph B until this gate passes.

## Phase 4 - Subgraph B

`ssim_forward`, `ssim_backward`

## Phase 5 - Subgraph C

`rasterize_backward_*` for all ref scheduler variants, then `fused_projection_backward_optimizer`.

## Phase 6 - Subgraph G

Morton kernels, required before E end-of-step reorder.

## Phase 7 - Subgraph E

Default ADC chain per `shader-pipeline.md`; reuses D and G.

## Phase 8 - Subgraph F

MCMC is deferred until Phase 7 is complete and integrated. Do not interleave E/F porting.

## Phase 9 - E2E Smoke

Tiny scene and loss trend after isolated subgraph gates pass.

## Rules

- Fixture-first and binding-contract checks at every kernel.
- Do not wire `train_step` until Phases 3-7 gates pass.
- Do not skip Phases 1-2 to test rasterize first.
- Mark stages done using SPIR-V names from the shader-pipeline shader index.

## Deferred Non-Kernel Scope

Python bindings, viewer, perf scheduler, and Thompson scheduling optimization stay out of isolated kernel port tasks.
